Consider the following C function:

int fun1(int n) {
    int i, j, k, p, q = 0;
    for (i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
        p = 0;
        for (j = n; j > 1; j = j/2) ++p;
        for (k = 1; k < p; k = k * 2) ++q;
    }
    return q;
}

Which one of the following most closely approximates the return value of the function fun1?

A. n^2
B. n(log n)^2
C. n log n
D. n log(log n)

Consider the following C function:

int fun(int n) {
    int x = 1, k;
    if (n == 1) return x;
    for (k = 1; k < n; ++k)
        x = x + fun(k) * fun(n - k);
    return x;
}

The return value of fun(5) is ______.

Consider the following C function:

void convert(int n) {
    if (n < 0)
        printf("%d", n);
    else {
        convert(n / 2);
        printf("%d", n % 2);
    }
}

Which one of the following will happen when the function convert is called with any positive integer n as argument?

A. It will print the binary representation of n and terminate
B. It will print the binary representation of n in the reverse order and terminate
C. It will print the binary representation of n but will not terminate
D. It will not print anything and will not terminate
